tags: when will this kind of self-congratulatory grade A garbage stop?
while i have other issues with that movie i can't stand reading another 'mcu introduces their first canonically gay character' article
summary: i’m gonna be honest – it really, really irks me that the russos actually think they did something with the “first lgbt+...
body:
i’m gonna be honest – it really, really irks me that the russos actually think they did something with the “first lgbt+ character in the mcu.” all it ended up being was a random throwaway character – a dude, portrayed by joe russo, in the beginning of the movie who talked about his date with another guy. as much as i appreciate what little they did… this just ain’t it. it’s too little, too late.

lgbt+ people shouldn’t exist in film as a trope or, essentially, a prop in the background: we aren’t something for you to use to get praise for your attempts at inclusivity and/or get the lgbt+ community interested in what little you have to offer. representation isn’t or will ever be extras with a few seconds of screentime in a major franchise film. if you’re gonna ‘hype up’ a lgbt+ character, give them a more substantial role. don’t throw them to the sidelines so fucking blatantly and continue a pattern of token characters we still continue to see.

“thank you, my queen.” You smile to Hela and in return she has a smirk on her face.

so they might not actually be true
but the first time round i felt that steve just ditched bucky
still not okay with it though
if anything bucky should have been the one to go back and live a full life
summary:
BUCKY KNEW
Bucky knew that Steve wouldn’t come back. When Steve is about to take the stones back, Bucky says “I’ll miss you”,...
body:
BUCKY KNEW

Bucky knew that Steve wouldn’t come back. When Steve is about to take the stones back, Bucky says “I’ll miss you”, and then when Steve doesn’t return, Bucky isn’t surprised to see him on the bench

It’s why he sends Sam to Steve instead of going himself. HE KNEW.

At some point off screen, they must have had a discussion about it, and that’s why Bucky isn’t annoyed that Steve left him, and therefore Steve didn’t completely disregard Bucky when he stayed back in time with Peggy
